HEADWORD: checkerbloom
<hw>checkerbloom</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a perennial purple-flowered
wild mallow of West North America (<spn>Sidalcea malviflora</spn>) that
is also cultivated.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> wild hollyhock, <spn>Sidalcea
malviflora</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
